nite sum of functions with summable sup norm is continuous if each individual\nfunction is. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/Series.lean#L83-L89","name":"continuousOn_tsum","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/Series.html#continuousOn_tsum","doc":"An infinite sum of functions with summable sup norm is continuous on a set if each individual\nfunction is. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/Series.lean#L74-L78","name":"tendstoUniformly_tsum_nat","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/Series.html#tendstoUniformly_tsum_nat","doc":"An infinite sum of functions with summable sup norm is the uniform limit of its partial sums.\nVersion with index set `ℕ`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/Series.lean#L67-L69","name":"tendstoUniformly_tsum","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/Series.html#tendstoUniformly_tsum","doc":"An infinite sum of functions with summable sup norm is the uniform limit of its partial sums.\nVersion with general index set. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/Series.lean#L58-L62","name":"tendstoUniformlyOn_tsum_nat","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/Series.html#tendstoUniformlyOn_tsum_nat","doc":"An infinite sum of functions with summable sup norm is the uniform limit of its partial sums.\nVersion relative to a set, with index set `ℕ`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/Series.lean#L42-L53","name":"tendstoUniformlyOn_tsum","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/